  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is described in the supporting technical report and discussed throughout the validation narrative; however, formal UQ artifact links are not uniformly attached to all validation result records. Seven credibility factors were assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. Decision: Accepted pending resolution of outstanding factor gaps.",
