      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in vitro measurement at the nominal design operating point. Predicted NIH = 0.0041 g/100L; measured NIH = 0.0038 ± 0.0004 g/100L. Relative error 7.9%. Monte Carlo sampling over blood viscosity and power-law rheology parameters was performed across 500 realizations; the resulting prediction interval is reported in the technical appendix. Uncertainty sources include inlet velocity profile variability and red blood cell fragility distribution.",
